  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "一筆でラインを消そう！同じ色の横列を作ってボードをクリアします。全365のパズルがあり、さまざまなモードや特別なタイトルがあなたの頭を挑戦させます。ルールに慣れて、いくつかのレベルで練習したり、時間との勝負を楽しんだり、自分だけのパズルを作成してみましょう！",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "Polarium Advance is a 2005 puzzle video game developed by Mitchell Corporation and published by Nintendo for the Game Boy Advance. Despite starting development before it, it is not a sequel to Polarium on the Nintendo DS. It was released in Japan in October 2005 and Europe in March 2006, with Atlus releasing it in North America in November 2006. The objective of the game is similar to that of its predecessor; black and white tiles fill a grid, and by drawing a single line in the grid, tiles can be flipped from black to white (or vice versa).  Solid, horizontal lines of all black or all white tiles are erased, and the goal is to erase the entire grid in this manner. \nThe game received a re-release on the Wii U's Virtual Console. The game was planned to be released in China for the iQue Game Boy Advance system, but this release was cancelled due to high piracy. However, the Chinese translation was fully completed, and it can be played through emulation. However, the game's DS predecessor was released in China.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
  ],
